  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "When a Ceph node is being removed from the cluster, the OSD pod waits for the usage or PG count of the OSDs to start going down, indicating that rebalancing has started before it moves on to the next step.  If the usage is 0 though, this value will never go down and the wait will eventually time out with an error similar to `last error: current used space and pg count for osd.94 has not decreased still`.\r\n\r\nThis should be an easy fix to just skip to the next step if initial usage and PG count is 0.\r\nThis was first mentioned by @dimm0 in https://github.com/rook/rook/issues/1687#issuecomment-386766763.",
